From the previous question, we know that

\begin{align*}
T(t) - 19 =  -16e^{kt}
\end{align*}

where

$\displaystyle k = \frac{-\ln(2)}{30}$

Searching for when $T(t) = 16$ yields

\begin{align*}
16-19 &= -16e^{kt} \\
-3 &= -16e^{kt} \\
\frac{3}{16} &= e^{kt} \\
\ln(3/16) &= kt\\
\ln(3/16) &= \frac{-\ln(2)t}{30} \\
t &= -30\frac{\ln(3/16)}{\ln(2)} \\
t &= 30\frac{\ln(16/3)}{\ln(2)} 
\end{align*}

completing the question.
